seal     : When food runs out, tens of thousands of lone amoebae — each a separate single-celled creature — stream together by chemical pulse into one body: a crawling slug, then a stalk that sacrifices a fifth of its cells so the rest can rise as spores. A many-celled animal that is really a society, voting with chemistry to become one.
